    <p>*This <nobr>Citi<sup>&reg;</sup> / AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> card offer is only valid for new applicants for a <nobr>Citi<sup>&reg;</sup> / AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> account made pursuant to this offer and is not available to existing cardmembers or recent applicants for a <nobr>Citi<sup>&reg;</sup> / AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> credit card.</p>

    <p>&dagger; For benefit to apply, the <nobr>Citi<sup>&reg;</sup> / AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> account must be open 7 days prior to air travel AND, reservation must include the primary cardmember's <nobr>American Airlines AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> number 7 days prior to air travel. If your credit card account is closed for any reason, these benefits will be cancelled. Eligible <nobr>Citi<sup>&reg;</sup> / AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> primary cardmembers may check one bag free of charge when traveling to domestic destinations on flights marketed and operated by <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr>, or on flights marketed by <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> and operated by <nobr>Envoy&nbsp;Air</nobr>, Inc., SkyWest Airlines, Inc., ExpressJet Airlines, Inc., Republic Airline Inc., or Chautauqua Airlines, Inc. This benefit will not be available for travel on US Airways flights or on codeshare flights booked with an <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> flight number but operated by another airline. For the <nobr>Citi<sup>&reg;</sup> / AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> card, up to four customers traveling with the eligible primary cardmember will also get their first checked bag free of charge if they are listed in the same reservation. Waiver does not apply to overweight or oversized bags. This benefit cannot be combined with any existing AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup> elite program benefits, including any waiver of baggage charges. Please see <a href="http://aa.com" target="_blank" title="aa.com">aa.com</a> for baggage weight and size restrictions. Additional terms, conditions and restrictions may apply. Applicable terms and conditions are subject to change without notice.</p>

    <p>++ Each pass is valid for one day for one person and is non-refundable, non-changeable and non-transferable. Passes must be presented at time of visit. Passes may not be bartered or sold other than by <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> <nobr>Admirals&nbsp;Club<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> and will become void upon such transfer. Passes are not valid for use at the facilities of other airlines with which <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> and US Airways may have reciprocal lounge or club access privileges. Due to security restrictions and lounge location in certain airports, not all lounges may be accessed at the destination airport. “Pass holder” must be at least 18 years of age and hold a same-day ticket for airline travel that allows clearance through security for flight departure and access to the <nobr>Admirals&nbsp;Club<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> or US Airways Club<sup>&reg;</sup> lounge. Up to 3 children under 18 years of age admitted for free when accompanied with the adult “Pass holder”. Use of the <nobr>Admirals&nbsp;Club<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> and US Airways Club<sup>&reg;</sup> facilities is subject to all rules and conditions set by <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> and US Airways, including without limitation, all policies set forth in the Membership Terms and Conditions.</p>
    
    <p>1. <nobr>American Airlines AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> miles will appear as a bonus in your AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup> account <nobr>8&#45;10 weeks</nobr> after you have met the purchase requirements. Only the primary cardmember is eligible to earn miles. Purchases exclude returned goods and services, cash advances, convenience checks, transferred balances, credits, fees and interest charges.</p>

    <p>2. For benefit to apply, the <nobr>Citi<sup>&reg;</sup> / AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> account must be open 7 days prior to air travel AND, reservation must include the primary cardmember's <nobr>American Airlines AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> number 7 days prior to air travel. If your credit card account is closed for any reason, these benefits will be cancelled. The Group 1 boarding benefit on your <nobr>Citi<sup>&reg;</sup> / AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> card will display at the top of your <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> boarding pass as Group 1. Eligible <nobr>Citi<sup>&reg;</sup> / AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> cardmembers will have Group 1 boarding on flights operated and marketed by <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr>, or on flights marketed by <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> and operated by <nobr>Envoy&nbsp;Air</nobr>, Inc., SkyWest Airlines, Inc., ExpressJet Airlines, Inc., Republic Airline Inc. or Chautauqua Airlines, Inc. This benefit will not be available for travel on US Airways flights or on codeshare flights booked with an <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> flight number but operated by another airline. Group 1 boarding will only be printed on the top of the boarding pass of the eligible <nobr>Citi<sup>&reg;</sup> / AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> primary credit cardmember. Up to four customers traveling with and listed in the same reservation as the <nobr>Citi<sup>&reg;</sup> / AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> primary credit cardmember are eligible for Group 1 boarding. Applicable terms and conditions are subject to change without notice.</p>

    <p>3. Eligible <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> purchases are items billed by <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> as merchant of record, including US Airways codeshare flights (a flight with a US Airways number but operated by <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr>) booked through <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> channels (<a href="http://aa.com" target="_blank" title="aa.com">aa.com</a>, <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> reservations, and <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> airport and city ticket counters). Miles earned will be posted to the primary cardmember’s AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup> account. Products or services that do not qualify are purchases of tickets on US Airways or <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> codeshare flights (a flight with an <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> number but operated by US Airways)  booked through US Airways channels, car rentals, hotel reservations, <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> Vacations packages, purchases of <nobr>American Airlines AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> miles, duty free purchases and AA Cargo<sup class="SM_footer_sup">SM</sup>. AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup> bonus miles will be posted to your AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup> account in <nobr>8&#45;10 weeks.</nobr></p>


    <p>4. For the Citi<sup>&reg;</sup> / AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup> Platinum Select<sup>&reg;</sup> Card: The standard variable APR for purchases – 13.99%, 17.99% or 21.99% based on your creditworthiness. Balance transfers are also subject to the standard purchase APR. The standard variable APR for cash advances - 25.24%. The variable Penalty APR is up to 29.99% and may be applied if you make a late payment or make a payment that is returned. The annual fee for this card is $95. However, this fee is waived for the first 12 months. Minimum interest charge - $0.50. Fee for foreign purchases - 3% of each purchase transaction in U.S. dollars. Cash advance fee - Either $10 or 5% of the amount of each cash advance, whichever is greater. Balance transfer fee - Either $5 or 3% of the amount of each transfer, whichever is greater.</p>

    <p>5. AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup> miles are earned on purchases, except returned goods and services, cash advances, convenience checks, transferred balances, credits, fees and interest charges. Only the primary cardmember is eligible to earn miles.</p>

    <p>6. Earn a $100 <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> Flight Discount when you spend $30,000 or more in purchases on your <nobr>Citi<sup>&reg;</sup> / AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> credit card during your cardmembership year (each 12 month period prior to your anniversary date) and your account remains open for at least 45 days after your anniversary. The Flight Discount expires one year from date of issue. The Flight Discount is redeemable toward the initial electronic ticket purchase of air travel wholly on flights marketed and operated by <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr>, or on flights marketed by <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> and operated by <nobr>Envoy&nbsp;Air</nobr>, Inc., SkyWest Airlines, Inc., ExpressJet Airlines, Inc., Republic Airline Inc., or Chautauqua Airlines, Inc. for itineraries sold and originating in the U.S., Puerto Rico and U.S. Virgin Islands. The Flight Discount is also redeemable for air travel on any <b>one</b>world<sup>&reg;</sup> carrier or <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> codeshare flight (this includes US Airways flights booked as <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> codeshare flights). The Flight Discount is redeemable online at <a href="http://aa.com" target="_blank" title="aa.com">aa.com</a>. The Flight Discount is redeemable only toward the purchase of the base air fare and directly associated taxes, fees and charges that are collected as part of the fare calculation for travel. The Flight Discount may not be used for flight products and/or services that are sold separately or non-flight products and/or services sold by <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr>. If the ticket price is greater than the value of the Flight Discount, the difference must be paid only with a credit, debit or charge card, or with <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> Gift Cards. If travel booked with the Flight Discount is cancelled or changed by the cardmember, the Flight Discount will be forfeited and the cardmember will be responsible for any applicable fare difference and the applicable change fee. The Flight Discount will not be replaced for any reason. The Flight Discount is non-refundable, may not be sold and has no cash redemption value. If the $30,000 purchase requirement was met during your cardmembership year and your account remains open for at least 45 days after your anniversary, please allow <nobr>8&#45;12 weeks</nobr> for the Flight Discount delivery.</p>

    <p>7. For benefit to apply, your <nobr>Citi<sup>&reg;</sup> / AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> account must be open and active at the time of redemption. The <nobr>American Airlines AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> bonus miles the primary cardmember earns through this benefit will be based on 10% of the total AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup> miles the primary cardmember redeems each month during the calendar year. The maximum number of AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup> bonus miles that can be earned annually from this benefit is 10,000 AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup> bonus miles per calendar year and per AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup> account, regardless of how many AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup> miles you redeem in that calendar year. This benefit only applies to AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup> miles redeemed from the primary cardmember's AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup> account. Discover all the ways to redeem AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup> miles at <a href="http://aa.com/redeem" target="_blank" title="aa.com/redeem">aa.com/redeem</a>. Please allow <nobr>6&#45;8 weeks</nobr> after your redemption for the <nobr>American Airlines AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> bonus miles to post to the primary cardmember’s AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup> account.</p>

    <p>8. <nobr>Citi<sup>&reg;</sup> / AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> cardmembers will receive a 25% savings on in-flight purchases of food, beverages, and headsets on flights operated by <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> when purchased with their <nobr>Citi<sup>&reg;</sup> / AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup></nobr> card. Savings do not apply to any other in-flight purchases, such as wireless internet access, SkyMall&trade; and DutyFree. Offer is available on eligible flights as long as supplies last. This benefit will not be available for travel on US Airways flights or on codeshare flights booked with an <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> flight number but operated by another airline. Savings will appear as a statement credit <nobr>6&#45;8 weeks</nobr> after the transaction is posted to the cardmember's credit card account. Additional terms, conditions and restrictions may apply. Applicable terms and conditions are subject to change without notice.</p>

    <p>American Airlines reserves the right to change AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup> program rules, regulations, travel awards and special offers at any time without notice and to end the AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup> program with six months notice. Any such changes may affect your ability to use the mileage awards or credits that you have accumulated. Members may not be able to obtain all offered awards at all times or use awards for all destinations or on all flights. AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup> travel awards, mileage accrual and special offers are subject to government regulations. Unless specified, AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup> miles earned through this promotion/offer do not count towards elite status qualification or AAdvantage Million Miler<sup class="SM_footer_sup">SM</sup> status. <nobr>American&nbsp;Airlines</nobr> is not responsible for products or services offered by other participating companies. For complete details about the AAdvantage<sup>&reg;</sup> program, visit <a href="http://aa.com/aadvantage" target="_blank" title="aa.com/aadvantage">aa.com/aadvantage</a>.</p>
